{"questionId":"4919","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Calcium carbonate reacts with hydrochloric acid.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">CaCO<sub>3</sub>(s) + 2HCl(aq) → CaCl<sub>2</sub>(aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O(l) + CO<sub>2</sub>(g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The results of a series of experiments in which the concentration of HCl was varied are shown below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4466/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-07_om_11.18.37.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/X04.b\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Draw the best fit line for the reaction excluding point D.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4487/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-07_om_14.39.56.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/04.b.ii/M\"></p>\n<p>straight line going through the origin <strong><em>AND </em></strong>as close to A, B, C as is reasonably&nbsp;possible</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"4919","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ1.4b.ii","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Draw the best fit line for the reaction excluding point D.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.2 Graphical techniques","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}